Constructor’s Notes

I made this puzzle way back in December 2014, so I don’t remember too much about the construction process. I do remember building out the upper-left corner and being pretty appalled by the Tetris-style arrangement of black squares, but going with it because I thought the fill was worth it. I actually had some back and forth with Will and Joel about KIND EYES in the southeast. I had seeded the corner with that entry, but they initially asked me to rework things to eliminate it. I wrote an impassioned, 300-word email to defend the answer, and they agreed to run it. I’m glad they did ... I hope solvers agree!

Your thoughts?